\vfill

\title{Universality and Scaling at the Onset of
Quantum Black Hole Formation}

\vfill

\author{Andrew Strominger,\foot{andy@denali.physics.ucsb.edu}}

\address{Department of Physics \break University of California at
\break Santa Barbara, CA 93106-9530}

\andauthor{L\'arus Thorlacius,\foot{larus@nsfitp.itp.ucsb.edu}}

\address{Institute for Theoretical Physics
\break University of California at
\break Santa Barbara, CA 93106-4030}

\vfill

\abstract
{\singlespace
In certain two-dimensional models, collapsing matter forms a
black hole if and only if the incoming energy flux exceeds the
Hawking radiation rate.  Near the critical threshold, the black
hole mass is given by a universal formula in terms of the
distance from criticality, and there exists a scaling solution
describing the formation and evaporation of an arbitrarily
small black hole.}

%PACS numbers: 04.70.Dy
\vfill\endpage

